#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_TEST_BUILD_DEPENDS.rst:2
msgid "CMAKE_TEST_BUILD_DEPENDS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_TEST_BUILD_DEPENDS.rst:8
msgid ""
":generator:`FASTBuild` and the :ref:`Makefile Generators` gained support for "
"``test_prep/<name>`` targets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_TEST_BUILD_DEPENDS.rst:11
msgid ""
"Enable ``test_prep/<name>`` build targets for tests added by :command:"
"`add_test` when using the :ref:`Ninja Generators`, :generator:`FASTBuild`, "
"or :ref:`Makefile Generators`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_TEST_BUILD_DEPENDS.rst:15
msgid ""
"When this variable is set to a true value, CMake generates a ``test_prep/"
"<name>`` target for each eligible test and a ``test_prep/all`` target for "
"all such tests. Building these targets ensures the test executable, targets "
"referenced by test command generator expressions, and explicit "
"``BUILD_DEPENDS`` entries are up-to-date before the test runs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_TEST_BUILD_DEPENDS.rst:21
msgid ""
"Tests whose names are not valid target names are excluded from this "
"behavior. If multiple tests in different directories share the same name, "
"their dependencies are merged into a single ``test_prep/<name>`` target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_TEST_BUILD_DEPENDS.rst:25
msgid ""
"With the :ref:`Makefile Generators`, a ``BUILD_DEPENDS`` file is built by "
"building the target whose build produces it.  A generated file that is not "
"the unique output of a single target is reported with a warning, and a test "
"whose name contains a ``:`` character is excluded because it cannot be "
"expressed as a Makefile target."
msgstr ""
